      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__common_1gab898ebdd11950907ac66e978d2bd8d92" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XUtil_MemoryTest32</definition>
        <argsstring>(u32 *Addr, u32 Words, u32 Pattern, u8 Subtest)</argsstring>
        <name>XUtil_MemoryTest32</name>
        <param>
          <type>u32 *</type>
          <declname>Addr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Words</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Pattern</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u8</type>
          <declname>Subtest</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Performs a destructive 32-bit wide memory test. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Addr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the region of memory to be tested. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Words</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the length of the block. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Pattern</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the constant used for the constant pattern test, if 0, 0xDEADBEEF is used. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Subtest</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the test selected. See <ref refid="xutil_8h" kindref="compound">xutil.h</ref> for possible values.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para></para></simplesect>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_MEMTEST_FAILED is returned for a failure</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS is returned for a pass</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
Used for spaces where the address range of the region is smaller than the data width. If the memory range is greater than 2 ** width, the patterns used in XUT_WALKONES and XUT_WALKZEROS will repeat on a boundary of a power of two making it more difficult to detect addressing errors. The XUT_INCREMENT and XUT_INVERSEADDR tests suffer the same problem. Ideally, if large blocks of memory are to be tested, break them up into smaller regions of memory to allow the test patterns used not to repeat over the region tested. </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/proj/xhdsswstaff1/bhawanas/patch_integration/auto_jobs/esw_github_doxy/git/2026.1/embeddedsw/XilinxProcessorIPLib/drivers/common/src/xutil.h" line="133" column="1" bodyfile="/proj/xhdsswstaff1/bhawanas/patch_integration/auto_jobs/esw_github_doxy/git/2026.1/embeddedsw/XilinxProcessorIPLib/drivers/common/src/xutil_memtest.c" bodystart="72" bodyend="377"/>
